.TH "vmw_resources_reserve" 9 "vmw_resources_reserve" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_resources_reserve \- Reserve all resources on the sw_context's resource list.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_resources_reserve
.BI "(struct vmw_sw_context *sw_context "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sw_context" 12
Pointer to the software context.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that since vmware's command submission currently is protected by the
cmdbuf mutex, no fancy deadlock avoidance is required for resources, since
only a single thread at once will attempt this.
